title.narrative: Programme de renforcement de la prévention et de la prise en charge du VIH/SIDA et de la tuberculose en RCA

description.narrative: Central African Republic - TB/HIV - La Croix-Rouge française - CRF. This program has the following goals: Contribute to improving the health of the Central African population by accelerating the fight against HIV and ending the AIDS epidemic through quality interventions implemented in full respect of human rights and dignity.. Reduce TB-related mortality by 35% by 2021 compared to 2015 levels.. The objectives of this program are: Accelerate access to ARV treatment for PLHIV, children and adolescents (10-19 y.-o.) by 2020. Accelerate the elimination of mother-to-child transmission of HIV by 2020. Reinforce prevention among adolescents, youth and key populations by 2020. Reinforce testing and adequate treatment among new cases of TB by 2020. Reinforce testing and adequate treatment among MDR-TB cases by 2020. Reinforce treatment of co-infected TB-HIV cases by 2020
